  "text": "Java PathFinder started out as an explicit-state model checker for Java bytecode [CITATION_1] . It can thus perform model checking on programs written in languages that can target the JVM. Its initial implementation approach was to convert Java bytecode to Promela to be analyzed with the Spin model checker [CITATION_2] . But since then, it checks Java byte code directly.",
